The paper presents a new model of incomplete information games without private information, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The players use a distributionally robust optimization approach to cope with payoff uncertainty, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computation of equilibria, which involves optimization and control theory (cs.SY) and linear algebra (cs.DS).
